### Automated  Install using the script ###
For Automated installs just use the script install.sh
This only installs the Fonts not the Themes and icons

##### Manual Installation
The packages needed for this config to work 


sudo pacman -S xfce4-panel xfdesktop xfce4-settings xfce4-power-manager xfce4-docklike-plugin bc openbox obconf playerctl picom parcellite numlockx rofi polybar lxappearance betterlockscreen

Then copy the files inside the config folder to .config folder
Also Open the .config/polybar/scripts

Copy the files from the usr/bin to /usr/bin
Then extract the fonts.tar.gz to the /usr/share/fonts/ 

##Optional Icons,themes,
Extract the themes theme,Icons to /usr/share/icons ,/usr/share/themes

###Lcokscreeen Rofi
Copy the cache dirs files to .cache dir

##For the Brightness module to work
Then open the etc/udev/rules.d/90-backlight.rules with your text editor and replace username with your linux username

###Optional If you want to replace bash with zsh follow this
sudo pacman -S zsh zsh-autosuggestions zsh-history-substring-search zsh-syntax-highlighting
copy the zsh to home directory

Now Reboot and enjoy
